title.narrative: Investing for impact against tuberculosis and HIV

description.narrative: Haiti - TB/HIV - Population Services International - PSI HQ. This program has the following goals: By 2020, reduce the proportion of new HIV infections by 45% in the general population and key populations. By 2020, increase the survival rate to 90% for adults and children living with HIV under ARV, 12 months after initiating ART. By 2020, reduce morbidity by 10% and mortality by 15% caused by tuberculosis. By 2020, strengthen the health system. The objectives of this program are: By 2020, increase to at least 90% the proportion of key populations who have low-risk behaviour and sexual practices. By 2020, ensure 100% coverage of sero-positive pregnant women and children born to sero-positive mothers through the set of services aimed at reducing mother-to-child HIV transmission. By 2020, increase to at least 90% the proportion of adults and children living with HIV availing of medical, psychological and social health care. Maintain at least 85% therapeutic success rate for PTB+ and PTB- between 2018 and 2020. By 2020, increase to at least 85% the proportion of MDR-TB cases that are diagnosed and treated. By 2020, contribute to strengthening the health system
